    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Prerequisite: Pact of the Blade feature</em></p><p>You can use any weapon you summon with your Pact of the Blade feature as a spellcasting focus for your warlock spells and you can perform the somatic components of spells even your hands are full as long as at least one hand is wielding your pact weapon.</p><p>In addition, the weapon gains a +1 bonus to its attack and damage rolls, unless it is a magic weapon that already has a bonus to those rolls. Beginning at 7th level in warlock the pact weapon bonus increases to +2. Finally at 11th level in warlock the pact weapon bonus increases to +3.</p><p>Finally, the weapon you conjure can be a shortbow, longbow, light crossbow, or heavy crossbow.</p>",
